value.0: Crudely crafted out of stone, this altar was meant for rituals.

Value.value: You're not for sure what type of rituals this altar was used for, but what you can tell about the altar and the surrounding area is that the rituals weren't for anything good.

Humans skulls piled symbolically on top of the altar, a broken crystal tomb resting directly in front of you, old blood splattered around the altar, and burnt human corpses resting on tall spikes either side of you all lead you to believe that the Troglodytes have been up to some ritual to release a terrible creature.

You are able to tell that this altar was used once and only once. What remains is symbolic, judging by the human skulls styled into a pyramid atop the altar. Further inspection of the nearby area leads you truly to believe that what broke from the crystal before you was something large and dangerous. With your knowledge you have begun to realize the Troglodytes have attempted to revive one of their Paragons; a Troglodyte of ancient times far stronger than the creatures you have fought so far and much more intelligent.
